  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nWhat the issue is, in broad strokes.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nCalling same logic fails when using async/await paradigm \r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nexpected to be the same \r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nfailure to provide the result\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Mac\r\n* Ethereum client: ganache\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 4.1.13\r\n* node version (`node --version`):v8.11.1\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.0.1\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n  const user1 = accounts[4]\r\n\r\n  before(async () => {\r\n    myToken = await MyToken.deployed()\r\n    owner = await myToken.owner.call()\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  it('should deposit and reflect on user balance', async () => {\r\n    await myToken.deposit.call(user1, 20000)\r\n    let balance = await myToken.balanceOf.call(user1)\r\n    assert.equal(balance.valueOf(), 20000, `The balance 20000 was not reflected.`)\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  it('should deposit and reflect on user balance Sync', () => {\r\n    return MyToken.deployed().then(function (instance) {\r\n      myToken = instance\r\n      return myToken.deposit(user1, 20000)\r\n    }).then(function () {\r\n      return myToken.balanceOf.call(user1)\r\n    }).then(function (user1balance) {\r\n      assert.equal(user1balance, 20000, 'The balance 20000 was not reflected.')\r\n    })\r\n  })\r\n\r\n```\r\nAnd the result:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"816\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-07-10 at 6 44 36 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/574405/42521392-64355630-8471-11e8-93a2-1f56846ce263.png\">\r\n\r\nAny idea whats wrong?",
