    "body": "@moshebeeri Agree the docs are quite antiquated and confusing here, thank you for highlighting this.\r\n\r\n You actually don't need to use these postfixes at all with truffle - it automatically figures out which mode to call a function in. You might be interested in the note left [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/issues/1076#issuecomment-401497884) that explains the difference between making a `call` and sending a transaction. \r\n\r\nI'm going to close because the original issue seems resolved - we have plans to update and modernize our docs for the upcoming major release (V5). Will make sure to revisit the section in question and clear it up. Thanks.",
